<div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />They have nothing to do with H/Vblank.<br /></div><br />But the PPU does have to be in vblank for the CPU to write the palette; otherwise, glitches occur. And the PPU has to be in vblank or forced blank for the CPU to write to OAM, CHR RAM, or the nametable; otherwise, glitches occur.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Jul 11, 2010 9:52 am</p><hr />
